04/04/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Council of Europe (CoE) Secretary-General Terry Davis on Wednesday (April 4th) wrapped up a two-day visit to Belgrade, focused on preparations for Serbia's upcoming chairmanship of the CoE Committee of Ministers. 
The mandate runs from May to November. 
Meeting with Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic, Davis stressed that the post would provide an opportunity for Serbia to prove itself a leader in the region and Europe as a whole. 
Draskovic said Serbia's priorities would be democracy and human rights, combating terrorism and affirming the CoE's values in the Balkans. 
(Glas javnosti - 04/04/07; Beta, Tanjug - 03/04/07)
